createRandomMap() - Method in class gameplay.map.Map
The method createRandomMap creates a new random map which respects the following parameters: Terrain occupies 80% of the entire map, water the remaining 20% The map is not partitioned, every terrain cell can be reached from any other terrain cell The map is an island so it must be surrounded by water cells Water cells inside the map must be in groups of a minimum of 5 and a maximum of 15 cells Vegetation cells must occupy 40% of all terrain cells The map must contain 20 carrions
